# Scanner image .trivyignore — explicit CVE allowlist with rationale.
#
# Format: CVE-XXXX-NNNNN<TAB># reason
#
# Listed CVEs come from the debian:12-slim base layer and have no upstream
# fix available (fix_deferred or will_not_fix per the Debian security
# tracker). The scanner binary itself does not invoke perl or use zlib
# from these paths; the packages are transitive Debian deps brought in by
# `coreutils`. Removing them would require rebuilding on a leaner base
# image — tracked separately under REM-014 follow-up (Debian-slim →
# distroless audit). Until then, ignore the specific CVEs so trivy still
# gates against new findings.

CVE-2026-42496
CVE-2026-8376
CVE-2023-45853
